Taking care of your health never goes out of style! 
Cervical cancer is preventable, and HPV vaccination can help reduce the risk. HPV vaccination generally has a good safety profile. 

Just like any other vaccine, HPV vaccination may have mild side effects such as fever or pain at the injection site which are typically short-lived. 

Consult your gynaecologist today to learn more about HPV vaccination and take a step toward long-term protection. 

For more information, visit letsfighthpv.com. 

Please note: This information is for awareness purposes only. For personalized advice and details on HPV prevention, consult your gynaecologist. This message is issued in the public interest by MSD Pharmaceuticals.
